"lower digestive system-cecum appendix, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 25 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lower digestive system - cecum and appendix via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0d.. . "
"lower digestive system-cecum appendix, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 25 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lower digestive system - cecum and appendix via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0d.. restriction of cecum,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of cecum,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0dvh8zz. "

"lower digestive system-large intestine omentum, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 25 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lower digestive system - large intestine and omentum via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0d.. restriction of large intestine via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of large intestine via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0dve7dz. "lower digestive system-rectum anus, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 25 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lower digestive system - rectum and anus via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0d.. restriction of rectum via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of rectum via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0dvp8dz. "lower digestive system-rectum anus, natural or artificial opening-part b. this class includes one or more of 25 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lower digestive system - rectum and anus via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0d.. dilation of anus via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to dilation of anus via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0d7q8dz. "

"lower digestive system-small intestine, natural or artificial opening. this class includes one or more of 25 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lower digestive system - small intestine via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0d.. bypass ileum to sigmoid colon,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to bypass ileum to sigmoid colon,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0d1b8zn. "

"
